// NOTE: Integrated into the Fusion FSN tree for migration traceability.
// CONTENT:
// Fusion Vault: The Single Pane of Glass"Visibility is the precursor to control."The PhilosophyFusion Vault v4.0 moves beyond simple key generation. It is designed as a Security Console a unified interface where the invisible mathematics of Post-Quantum Cryptography become visible, measurable, and manageable.We built this interface to solve three specific problems in the “Harvest Now, Decrypt Later” era:1. The “Black Box” ProblemProblem: Traditional crypto libraries are silent. You call encrypt(), and it returns data. You have no idea if it used ECC, RSA, or Kyber, or how long it took. Solution: The Live Activity Feed. By visualizing the “Process ID” and “Latency” of every cryptographic operation, we prove to the operator that the 50/50 Standard is active. When you see a latency spike, you know the Lattice engine is working.2. The “Quantum Delta”Problem: Post-Quantum algorithms are heavier than classical ones. Operations teams need to know the cost of security. Solution: The Analytics Dashboard. We explicitly calculate and display the Quantum Delta, of the exact time difference between the Classical (P-256) and Quantum (MiniKyber) operations. This allows infrastructure teams to capacity plan for the post-quantum transition.3. Policy DriftProblem: Over time, configurations loosen. A developer might disable strict checks to fix a bug. Solution: The Configuration Guard. The Settings module includes a “Strict Mode” toggle. When enabled, the Guard logic inside the engine creates a hard stop for any non-hybrid handshake. It is not just a setting; it is a policy firewall.ArchitectureThe Vault is composed of four integrated layers:The Kernel: The FusionEngine (Java/WASM/JS) that performs the math.The Telemetry Bus: Captures start/end times and emits events to the feed.The Guard: A gatekeeper that validates key bundles before processing.The Shell: The React UI (FusionVault.tsx) that renders this state for humans.
